SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COLLECTIONS ARE USED FOR EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES
SCHOLARSHIPS, PROGRAM SERVICES AND CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS

THE COLLEGE ACCOUNTS FOR UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS BY PRESCRIBING A MINIMUM PROBABILITY THRESHOLD A TAX POSITION MUST MEET BEFORE A FINANCIAL STATEMENT INCOME TAX BENEFIT IS RECOGNIZED. THE MINIMUM THRESHOLD IS DEFINED AS A TAX POSITION, WHICH, BASED SOLELY ON ITS TECHNICAL MERITS, WOULD MORE LIKELY THAN NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE RELEVANT TAX AUTHORITY WITH KNOWLEDGE OF THE SAME FACTS. THE TAX BENEFIT TO BE RECOGNIZED IS THE LARGEST AMOUNT THAT HAS A GREATER THAN 50% PROBABILITY OF BEING REALIZED UPON ULTIMATE RESOLUTION. BASED ON ALL KNOWN FACTS AND CIRCUMSTANCES AND CURRENT TAX LAW, THE COLLEGE BELIEVES THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITION LIABILITIES AND RELATED ACCRUED INTEREST ARE NOT MATERIAL TO ITS FINANCIAL POSITION. AS OF MAY 31,2022, AND INCLUDING THE PREVIOUS THREE YEARS CONSIDERING EXTENSIONS, THE COLLEGE'S INCOME TAX RETURNS ARE OPEN AND SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES WITH RELEVANT JURISDICTION. SHOULD SUCH AN EXAMINATION TAKE PLACE, MANAGEMENT DOES NOT ANTICIPATE ANY SIGNIFICANT ISSUES RELATED TO THE OPEN YEARS.
GUILFORD COLLEGE HAS A POLICY OF CIVIL RIGHTS WHICH IS POSTED AROUND CAMPUS AND PUBLISHED IN THE STUDENT HANDBOOK. THE ADMINISTRATION STRICTLY FOLLOWS THIS POLICY.
THE COLLEGE RECEIVES FEDERAL FINANCIAL AID FROM THE US DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION
